# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values from your Supabase project
# (Project Settings → API). Never commit the real .env — it's git-ignored.
#
# Both variables are EXPO_PUBLIC_-prefixed, which means they're inlined into
# the shipped JS bundle. That's intentional and safe here — the Supabase
# anon key is designed to be public; access is governed by the Edge
# Function/RLS, the same trust model prototype/ios/App/AppConfig.swift uses.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY must NEVER appear in this file or anywhere in this app —
# it's a real secret and lives only in the Supabase function's own secret
# store. See docs/expo-first-run.md §6-8 for full setup.

EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-SUPABASE-ANON-KEY
